{
  "stem": "2004.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And it was a help because she took care of me when my father was busy in business.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "My mother sometimes helped along in business.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So I had somebody that could take care of me at the same time.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Samuel Mendel.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My mother's name was Dora.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My mother had a sister that lived in Krakow.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My father had two brothers.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he also had three sisters.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "My father was the oldest of them all.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] I also had a grandfather who lived in-- it was my father's father, paternal grandfather.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And he lived with his second wife in the Czech side of Cieszyn.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And of course, we visited him very quite frequently as well.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "He was also very active in the synagogue.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And he was actually the gabbai in the synagogue.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "That is-- a gabbai in the synagogue is sort of a-- what should I say-- he's sort of an honorary title of a caretaker.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "He distributes the [NON-ENGLISH] and so on and so forth, which was strictly voluntary.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, he was tall, always had a grey beard, very religious, and so was my father.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My father was also religious.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Whenever he did not go to temple, he always did his tefillin in the morning.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He never ate before he did his morning prayer.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we were quite observant.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Jewish life?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Well--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--in addition to going to Hebrew school, I was also going to Cheder, which was at that time more of-- getting more of a Talmudical education.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Unfortunately, not very much stuck to it, [LAUGHS] but nonetheless, I was eight years a student in Cheder.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So I was kept quite busy.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Between my Zionist organization, my normal school, my occasional English lesson, my Hebrew school, it didn't leave me too much time to play.",
      "word_count": 23
    }
  ],
